---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Games" description="Prediction game, lineup builder, quick-fire polls and leaderboard — Sportlad's free-to-enter engagement layer.">
  <h1 style="margin-top: 32px;">Games</h1>
  <p style="color: var(--muted); max-width: 60ch;">
    Free to enter, always — no stake, no gambling complication, just bragging rights (and one very good prize).
    This section builds out in the priority order below as the community grows — quickest, highest-frequency stuff first.
  </p>

  <div class="section-head"><h2>Free Prediction Game</h2></div>
  <div class="tool-card">
    <p><strong>Coming once the community's live.</strong> Weekly curated 5-10 fixtures, predict the outcomes via the Telegram bot, monthly leaderboard. Winner gets <strong>12 months free membership</strong>; top 5 get 1 month free.</p>
    <a class="btn" href="/community/">Join Telegram to get first access →</a>
  </div>

  <div class="section-head"><h2>What's Coming, in Order</h2></div>
  <div class="card-grid">
    <div class="card">
      <span class="tag">Phase 1</span>
      <h3>Quick-Fire Prediction Polls</h3>
      <p>"Who wins tonight?" before big matches, live result percentages. Cheapest to build, highest check-in frequency.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="tag">Phase 2</span>
      <h3>Lineup / Prediction Builder</h3>
      <p>Weekly "pick your XI" or predict-the-lineup for big fixtures — shares infrastructure with the main prediction game.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="tag">Phase 3</span>
      <h3>Beat the Lad</h3>
      <p>Predict the same fixture as Chris, compared head-to-head once it settles. Personal rivalry, low build cost.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="tag">Phase 4</span>
      <h3>Sport-Specific Mini-Games</h3>
      <p>F1 podium-order predictions; boxing method-of-victory and round predictions.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="tag">Phase 5</span>
      <h3>Live Matchday Threads</h3>
      <p>Running live-blog during big games — highest "feels alive" impact, launches once the daily rhythm's established.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="tag">Phase 6</span>
      <h3>Streaks &amp; Badges</h3>
      <p>Lightweight gamification rewarding consistency, not just winning — ties back to the discipline-over-luck positioning.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
